data.title: wanted articles
data.text:
List of linked-to articles that do not exist

"WP:WANTED" redirects here. For the Missing Articles WikiProject, see Wikipedia:WikiProject Missing encyclopedic articles.

See also: Special:WantedPages

This page lists articles that do (or did) not exist, but have incoming links from 20 or more other articles.

Note that "What links here" counts the number of pages in all namespaces that link to a given target, but this listing counts the number of pages in the main namespace only, including links from articles via templates. It does not include templates themselves. These are dealt with separately at Wikipedia:Templates with red links. See also Wikipedia:Requested articles. Note that subjects listed here might not necessarily meet our notability guidelines; if you are going to create an article on a subject listed here, please assess the subject's notability before creating the article.

This table was generated by User:Certes using this database script. Most of the links come from templates, however, as they have not been excluded. (This list was a test for a WikiProject, and includes only targets beginning with "A" or preceding characters such as digits. The code for targets beginning with other letters of the alphabet, can be found here. )
